Troubleshooting Tips
Draw.io won't start:

# Check if installed correctly
dpkg -l | grep drawio
# Reinstall if needed
sudo apt-get install -f
ATT&CK Navigator not loading:

# Check Node.js version
node --version  # Should be v18+
# Restart Navigator
cd attack-navigator
npm start
Python scripts fail:

# Verify Python version
python3 --version  # Should be 3.8+
# Install missing packages
pip3 install requests json datetime
JSON file not found errors:

Ensure you run scripts in order: discovery → assessment → redesign
Check current directory for generated JSON files
Use absolute paths if needed
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated the complete DARIOM methodology for enterprise security modeling. You learned to:

Discover enterprise architecture through systematic documentation
Assess threats using MITRE ATT&CK framework
Redesign security controls based on gap analysis
Implement improvements through structured roadmaps
Monitor security posture with defined procedures
The DARIOM approach provides a repeatable framework for continuous security improvement. Apply these techniques to real-world enterprise environments, adapting the methodology to specific organizational needs and compliance requirements.

Next Steps: Practice with different enterprise scenarios, integrate additional security tools, and automate more of the DARIOM workflow using Python scripts.
